@node U_Intro "Introduction"

  @{FG Shine}Introduction@{FG Text}
  ============
  
  This is a small tool that I wrote when I first started to test
  CrashTick, a Fidonet fileecho processor. I found that you could get TIC
  files containing a MAGIC field, and that field could be used to update
  your filerequest program to include new files under magic names.

  I've only tested it with CrashTick (the only TIC processor that I found
  that had an execute command if the MAGIC field was in a TIC file), but
  it should be possible to use it with other TIC processors as well.
@endnode

